# Database Restore → Alembic Upgrade (mandatory)

## Rule

After **any** PostgreSQL restore (`pg_restore`, `restore-db.ps1`, manual dump import), **always** run pending migrations from the **repository root**:

```powershell
cd fair-crm
python -m alembic upgrade head
```

Then restart dev runtime (`.\scripts\dev\reset-dev.ps1`).

`restore-db.ps1` runs this automatically at the end — if restore was manual, you must run it yourself.

## Why

A `.dump` carries the **schema version at backup time** (e.g. Alembic `0011`). Application code expects **current head** (e.g. `0015`). Missing columns cause API **500** errors.

## Symptom

- Admin → System → **Database Backups**: **"Failed to fetch"**, empty table, cannot create backup
- `GET /api/v1/admin/backups` → 500 (often missing `system_backups.backup_format` / `manifest_json` from migration `0014`)

## Verify

```powershell
python -m alembic current   # must show head revision
curl http://127.0.0.1:8001/health
```

## Do not

- Skip migrations because `/health` returns 200 — health does not validate schema
- Assume restore + backend restart is enough without `alembic upgrade head`
